"Thus rag'd the goddess : and, with fury fraught, The restless regions of the storms she sought, Where, in a spacious cave of living stone, The tyrant /Eolus, from his airy throne, With power imperial curbs the struggling winds, And sounding tempests in dark prisons binds ; This way, and that, the’ impatient captives tend, And, pressing for release, the mountains rend. High in his hall the’ undaunted monarch stands, And shakes his sceptre, and their rage commands ; Which did he not, their unresisted sway Would sweep the world before them in their way; Earth, air, andseas, throughempty space would roll, And heaven would fly before the driving soul. In fear of this, the father of the gods Confin'd their fury to those dark abodes, And lock’d them' safe within, oppress’d with"